               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" when="1994">1994</date>
                  <ab type="description">The ʾAmharā kǝllǝl is one of nine kǝllǝl that were
                     constituted following the promulgation of the Constitution of the Federal
                     Republic of <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop">Ethiopia</placeName> on the
                        <date>8th December 1994</date> The state is divided into the following
                     zones: <placeName ref="LOC6544NorthGondar">North Gondar</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC6574NorthSawa">North Šawā</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC6573NorthWallo">North Wallo</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC6575SouthGondar">South Gondar</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC6572SouthWallo">South Wallo</placeName>, <placeName ref="LOC6576WestGogg">West Goǧǧām</placeName>, and <placeName ref="LOC6577WestGondar">West Gondar</placeName>. Its capital is <placeName ref="LOC1721BaherD">Bāḥǝr Dār</placeName>. </ab>
               </note>
